To solve the warning "Unused function parameter," you can either remove or comment out the variable name in the function signature. This warning indicates that the function parameter named `_asset` is not being used within the function body.

Here are two possible solutions:

1. Remove the variable name:
```solidity
function withdraw(address) external returns (uint256 balance) {
  // Function implementation
}
```

2. Comment out the variable name:
```solidity
function withdraw(address /* _asset */) external returns (uint256 balance) {
  // Function implementation
}
```

Either of these solutions will silence the warning. However, if you intend to use the `_asset` parameter within the function implementation, ensure that you utilize it accordingly to avoid any unintended issues.
